WEBVTT

00:00.720 --> 00:04.230
Before there was sex,
before there was the city,

00:04.265 --> 00:07.540
there was just me-Carrie.
Carrie Bradshaw.

00:07.575 --> 00:09.122
And lots of things are changing...

00:09.157 --> 00:10.635
Larissa said that if I do a good job,

00:10.670 --> 00:13.100
she might hire me as her
full-time assistant over the summer.

00:13.135 --> 00:14.065
For all of us.

00:14.100 --> 00:16.020
- Do you like me?
- I do like you. So what?

00:16.055 --> 00:17.385
I like you too.

00:17.420 --> 00:18.320
Is that Mr. Bradshaw?

00:18.330 --> 00:20.220
Yeah,it is.
Let's go.

00:20.230 --> 00:23.670
We made out in your car
and got coffee a couple times.

00:23.705 --> 00:25.635
Kids don't really know
that I'm dating you.

00:25.670 --> 00:28.665
Admit it. It's always more fun
when you're with me.

00:28.700 --> 00:30.030
Did you give me that book
so I'd want to have sex with you?

00:31.030 --> 00:33.045
- No.
- I've been thinking about it a lot.

00:33.080 --> 00:35.070
Why do you have to think
so much about evything?

00:35.105 --> 00:36.342
Because that'who I am.

00:36.377 --> 00:37.545
If that's the way you feel

00:37.580 --> 00:39.450
then mabe we should just break up.

00:39.485 --> 00:41.740
If that'what you want, fine

00:45.000 --> 00:46.865
There's a brief moment when you wake up

00:46.900 --> 00:50.450
where you have no memories-
a blissful blank slate,

00:50.610 --> 00:52.240
a happy emptiness.

00:52.290 --> 00:53.825
But it doesn't last long,

00:53.860 --> 00:55.795
And you remember
exactly where you were

00:55.830 --> 00:57.695
and what you
were trying to forget-

00:57.730 --> 01:00.700
totally painful
gutly-wrenching break up.

01:02.160 --> 01:03.540
And the worst part-

01:03.680 --> 01:06.790
you have no one to be angry
with except yourself.

01:07.550 --> 01:09.330
Now the only thing
i could remember

01:09.340 --> 01:10.695
about me and Sebastian

01:10.730 --> 01:12.050
was how happy I was..

01:16.510 --> 01:17.980
And now I wasn't.

01:23.420 --> 01:24.955
Please!
You were not happy.

01:24.990 --> 01:26.640
You are always complaining
about him.

01:26.675 --> 01:27.880
And miserable.

01:27.890 --> 01:29.490
Absolutely miserable!

01:29.525 --> 01:30.145
I was?

01:30.180 --> 01:33.260
Totally, because he was
so needy and demanding

01:33.295 --> 01:35.032
and not even that cute.

01:35.067 --> 01:36.770
He's ugly, really. Oops.

01:37.050 --> 01:38.020
You went too far.

01:38.030 --> 01:38.855
Too far with what?

01:38.890 --> 01:40.135
We don't actually believe
any of these stuff.

01:40.170 --> 01:41.890
We're just trying to make you
feel better about the breakup.

01:41.925 --> 01:42.912
We feel awful for you guys.

01:42.947 --> 01:43.865
You were great together.

01:43.900 --> 01:46.870
- And right before prom.
- Breaking up before prom might

01:46.905 --> 01:49.840
actually be worse than getting dumped
near Valentine's Day.

01:50.240 --> 01:53.720
It's like walking to a giant spotlight
of pain and embarrassment.

01:53.800 --> 01:54.745
"Look at me, everyone.

01:54.780 --> 01:57.390
I have pretty dress
and no one to share it with"

01:57.425 --> 01:59.610
- Did you already buy the dress?
- I did.

01:59.645 --> 02:00.867
Maybe Mouse could ask some of

02:00.902 --> 02:02.261
West's cute basketball buddies

02:02.296 --> 02:03.620
what they're doing for prom.

02:03.770 --> 02:05.465
I'm not going to prom with West.

02:05.500 --> 02:08.350
Wait. Did I miss something?
Are-are you guys breaking up?

02:08.384 --> 02:11.530
No. It's because of my parents.

02:11.540 --> 02:12.665
Do they not like West?

02:12.700 --> 02:14.180
They do not know there is a West,

02:14.200 --> 02:16.180
and I would like
to keep it that way.

02:16.430 --> 02:17.735
They will never approve.

02:17.770 --> 02:20.590
I'm not exactly sure
how to ask this, but...

02:20.840 --> 02:22.600
Are your parents racist?

02:22.635 --> 02:24.360
Duh! Of course they are.

02:24.760 --> 02:26.365
Against anyone who isn't Chinese.

02:26.400 --> 02:27.870
How come we've
never heard about this?

02:27.905 --> 02:29.870
Because it sounds crazy.

02:29.880 --> 02:31.055
But my Chinese heritage is

02:31.090 --> 02:33.600
even more important
to them than Harvard.

02:33.635 --> 02:36.427
We're direct descendants
of the Qing Dynasty.

02:36.462 --> 02:39.220
- Okay, who cares?
- My parents, that's who.

02:39.840 --> 02:42.535
If I am ever allowed to date-

02:42.570 --> 02:44.675
and that probably can't happen
until after Harvard-

02:44.710 --> 02:48.000
then it has to be someone
who's also from the Qing Dynasty,

02:48.100 --> 02:50.510
like my parents'best friends' son...

02:51.360 --> 02:53.860
Eugene

02:54.030 --> 02:55.720
Eugene.
That does not sound promising.

02:55.755 --> 02:56.465
Trust me...

02:56.500 --> 02:58.910
when I say it is
the opposite of promising.

02:58.945 --> 03:01.320
- Does West know?
- I haven't told him.

03:01.355 --> 03:03.100
But I'm sure he'll understand.

03:03.350 --> 03:05.690
So none of us are going to the prom?

03:05.830 --> 03:08.460
Maybe we could still go-
the three of us.

03:08.630 --> 03:09.830
It could still be fun.

03:10.040 --> 03:11.115
Yeah, maybe.

03:11.150 --> 03:14.160
Like a trouple.
We'd make a very cute trouple.

03:14.170 --> 03:15.740
We would.

03:19.140 --> 03:20.440
Wait. Is that...

03:25.200 --> 03:26.200
Yeah.

03:29.010 --> 03:30.010
Simon

03:30.350 --> 03:32.810
Hi. I'm Noelle, Simon's fiancee.

03:33.250 --> 03:34.320
Maggie.

03:35.230 --> 03:36.640
Congratutions.

03:36.840 --> 03:39.550
Thanks. Super excited.

03:40.050 --> 03:41.800
Maggie's the chief's daughter.

03:42.800 --> 03:45.540
I don't wanna keep you guys
from your lunch, so...

03:45.575 --> 03:46.690
Of course.

03:47.590 --> 03:48.650
We'll see you around. Bye.

03:52.950 --> 03:54.710
Are you okay?

03:54.745 --> 03:56.470
I'm fine. Fine.

03:57.340 --> 03:58.405
Let's talk about prom plans.

03:58.440 --> 04:01.470
We should probably ask Walt
if he wants to come with us also.

04:01.570 --> 04:04.120
Yeah. Yeah.
We'll make it a party.

04:04.155 --> 04:05.570
I like the sound of a party.

04:12.590 --> 04:13.490
Heading to the gym?

04:13.525 --> 04:14.450
Yep.

04:14.590 --> 04:15.710
Is that cologne?

04:16.850 --> 04:19.930
Yeah. Yeah.
Drakkar noir.

04:20.240 --> 04:21.839
You're wearing cologne to the gym?

04:22.950 --> 04:25.250
Thers a guy there
who smells really bad.

04:25.285 --> 04:26.395
serious kills me.

04:26.430 --> 04:27.825
I just do my best to survive.

04:27.860 --> 04:29.480
That's why you'll never
catch me at the gym.

04:29.490 --> 04:32.680
Working out-not for me
but I'm glad you're joying it.

04:32.715 --> 04:33.370
I am.

04:33.380 --> 04:34.725
After I take the meditation class

04:34.760 --> 04:36.840
I realize how important
it is for me to have an outlet.

04:36.875 --> 04:38.920
You know, some place
where I can real go and just...

04:39.970 --> 04:40.690
let it all out.

04:40.725 --> 04:41.850
Oh, god.

04:46.270 --> 04:47.360
That is...

04:47.950 --> 04:50.080
That is so much better than the gym.

04:50.780 --> 04:52.110
It better be.

04:53.580 --> 04:55.120
I'd like to think
i'm a little more fun

04:55.155 --> 04:56.860
than free weights.

04:59.400 --> 05:00.080
You're trying
to leave me already?

05:00.100 --> 05:02.080
We just finished.

05:02.370 --> 05:05.390
For the third time.

05:07.600 --> 05:10.050
As much as I'd love to
have you spend the night,

05:10.085 --> 05:11.630
it's getting late.

05:12.160 --> 05:14.440
I mean, the gym has to close
at some point, right?

05:14.475 --> 05:15.820
I don't want you kids
to get suspicious.

05:15.855 --> 05:17.330
No, you're right I should get going.

05:17.365 --> 05:18.940
Don't wanna get busted.

05:19.050 --> 05:20.340
No, you're right.

05:21.110 --> 05:23.110
We are like couple of horny teenagers

05:23.145 --> 05:24.725
trying to get a quickie in.

05:24.760 --> 05:27.440
I hope the difference
between teenager time and adult time

05:27.475 --> 05:30.140
is that...
I'm not too quick.

05:30.175 --> 05:31.485
You are just right.

05:31.520 --> 05:33.280
I wonder how long we can keep it up.

05:33.315 --> 05:35.360
Or how long we should.

05:35.370 --> 05:36.400
What do you mean?

05:36.680 --> 05:39.595
Well, I... as much as I like

05:39.630 --> 05:41.750
being the other woman
to your little women,

05:41.785 --> 05:44.512
I... I just wonder if maybe we should-

05:44.547 --> 05:47.240
- Tell our kids that we're datin?
- Yeah.

05:47.410 --> 05:50.630
My girls lost their mom
less than a year ago.

05:51.260 --> 05:53.640
I mean, all they have now
are memories of us,

05:54.060 --> 05:56.525
and I just don't want them to

05:56.560 --> 05:58.640
feel like I'm disrespecting
those memories.

06:00.180 --> 06:03.410
And while one person was focused
on honoring the past...

06:04.230 --> 06:05.925
Another was diving into it.

06:05.960 --> 06:08.300
I can't believe you are going
to Kyoto for the summer

06:08.335 --> 06:09.415
to learn to be a geisha.

06:09.450 --> 06:11.600
Darling, in order to
embrace being a modern woman,

06:11.610 --> 06:13.950
you have to know the ways
of the traditional woman.

06:14.020 --> 06:15.820
And I hear they really know
how to pleasure a man.

06:15.830 --> 06:18.085
That is a skill
that every woman should know.

06:18.120 --> 06:20.960
Why do I have a feeling
you'll be teaching them a thing or two?

06:20.970 --> 06:22.530
Because you know me so well.

06:22.980 --> 06:23.535
I'm gonna miss you.

06:23.570 --> 06:26.470
Oh, please,
you are gonna "all about Eve" me.

06:26.505 --> 06:27.902
By the time I get back in July,

06:27.937 --> 06:29.265
you will have taken over my job

06:29.300 --> 06:31.655
and ensconced yourself in my office.

06:31.690 --> 06:33.700
I'd settle for getting to use
that phone of yours.

06:33.735 --> 06:36.210
I'd rather you take my job.
Hide this.

06:36.270 --> 06:38.160
So you'll keep an eye
on everyone for me

06:38.170 --> 06:39.825
while I'm gone, be my spy?

06:39.860 --> 06:41.445
And answer the phones.

06:41.480 --> 06:43.830
I still don't know
where that silly receptionist went.

06:43.865 --> 06:45.102
You went to her good-bye party.

06:45.137 --> 06:46.305
She move back to Dallas, remember?

06:46.340 --> 06:49.290
Oh, right. I always forget people
who don't like the city.

06:49.325 --> 06:50.595
They're just not worth remembering.

06:50.630 --> 06:52.580
Thanks to her,
i get to work here all summer

06:52.615 --> 06:54.905
as a real full-time receptionist.

06:54.940 --> 06:57.240
Hello? "Interview" magazine.
How may I help you?

06:57.275 --> 06:59.092
We're not paying.
You know that, right?

06:59.127 --> 07:00.875
I know.
I think I'll end up losing money

07:00.910 --> 07:03.060
having to take the train every day,
but I don't care.

07:03.095 --> 07:03.695
It's worth it.

07:03.730 --> 07:06.160
Sweets, you should stay
at my loft while I'm gone.

07:06.195 --> 07:08.200
The neighborhood is so skunge.

07:08.235 --> 07:08.755
It would be great

07:08.790 --> 07:10.545
to have someone
look after the place for me.

07:10.580 --> 07:12.510
Somehow I don't think
my dad would be too psyched

07:12.545 --> 07:13.735
about skungee, but...

07:13.770 --> 07:16.130
Say it's a gorgeous downtown loft

07:16.140 --> 07:18.860
with oodles of space for you
and the gorgeous Walt.

07:18.895 --> 07:20.412
You could live there together.

07:20.447 --> 07:22.093
That is such a generous offer.

07:22.128 --> 07:23.705
But I don't think I'm really

07:23.740 --> 07:26.370
ready to abandon
Castlebury entirely this summer.

07:27.100 --> 07:28.810
Haven't given up on the hair god?

07:29.270 --> 07:31.920
Don't fret.
The viking obviously adores you.

07:31.955 --> 07:33.302
Why else would he come to Manhattan

07:33.337 --> 07:35.393
and hang with a bunch
of fabulous gays

07:35.428 --> 07:37.450
and the hags who love them
if he didn't?

07:37.680 --> 07:39.940
And while I wished I wasn't alone...

07:39.950 --> 07:41.980
Are you serious?
I can't believe that.

07:42.015 --> 07:43.940
It appeared my sister wasn't.

07:44.030 --> 07:45.060
I actually forgot we did that.

07:45.095 --> 07:46.190
So funny.

07:46.660 --> 07:48.190
Carrie, hey.

07:50.790 --> 07:52.470
Carrie, hey.

